      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VrE1kciUIxD5",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "# From GAN to WGAN\n",
        ">A short explanation of what changed between original GAN and WGAN",
        "\n",
        "- toc: true \n",
        "- badges: true\n",
        "- comments: true\n",
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "LFu8CRRdI2G2",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "In [original version of GAN](https://arxiv.org/abs/1406.2661), the measure of real and generated examples was formulated as binary clasification: is it real or is it generated. Let's look at the simple case, where we have true distribution (in other words real examples) that consists of 0's. A perfect discriminator will return 1 when input to discriminator is 0 and 0 otherwise. Despite the fact that discriminator is doing great job at discriminating between real and generated, however, generator does not receive meaningful direction for improving. For example, generator output of 0.1 and 1 will be scored the same, even though 0.1 is much closer to real distribution. Let's see this in action."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5-wglga3QTqr",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
        "np.set_printoptions(suppress=False, precision=5)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "wftWB9mZ7Z2n",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Discriminator"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "qneqwsBBQASa",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "def d_loss(d_score_z, d_score_r):\n",
        "  batch_size = d_score_z.shape[0]\n",
        "  d_loss_z =tf.keras.losses.binary_crossentropy(tf.zeros(shape = [batch_size,1], dtype=tf.float32), d_score_z)\n",
        "  d_loss_r =tf.keras.losses.binary_crossentropy(tf.ones(shape = [batch_size,1], dtype=tf.float32), d_score_r)\n",
        "  return tf.reduce_mean(d_loss_z + d_loss_r)\n",
        "\n",
        "def define_discriminator(act=\"sigmoid\"):\n",
        "\n",
        "  d_optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.05)\n",
        "\n",
        "  # Discriminator\n",
        "  discriminator = tf.keras.models.Sequential()\n",
        "  discriminator.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(32, activation=\"relu\"))\n",
        "  discriminator.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(32, activation=\"relu\"))\n",
        "  discriminator.add(tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation=act))\n",
        "  return discriminator, d_optimizer"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "wJ-KeFRsVs-w",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "def train_discriminator(discriminator, d_optimizer, d_loss, batch_size = 64):\n",
        "  real_data = tf.zeros([batch_size, 1])\n",
        "  # Train discriminator till perfection\n",
        "  for i in range(1000):\n",
        "    with tf.GradientTape() as tape:\n",
        "      z = tf.random.normal(shape=[batch_size, 1])\n",
        "      d_score_z, d_score_r = discriminator(z), discriminator(real_data)\n",
        "      total_loss = d_loss(d_score_z, d_score_r)\n",
        "      if i % 100 == 0:\n",
        "        print(\"Total loss:\", total_loss.numpy(), \"Scores for real:\", d_score_r.numpy().mean(), \"Scores for generated:\", d_score_z.numpy().mean())\n",
        "      grads = tape.gradient(total_loss, discriminator.trainable_variables)\n",
        "      d_optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(grads, discriminator.trainable_variables))"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "lX-9S3XYgpY3",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "Disclaimer: we are creating artifial situation just to demonstrate underlying issue with using binary classification as loss for discriminator. In reality, we would not train discriminator in this fashion."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2cocPtVKylMy",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "outputId": "19d7b69f-d60c-4da8-c731-2179361b487c",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 201
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "discriminator, d_optimizer = define_discriminator()\n",
        "train_discriminator(discriminator, d_optimizer, d_loss)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
