    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "hndOtEfrkwZK",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "It works in this example, we can see that loss is decresing and generator output approaches 0. However, this works in this specific scenario, we can use euclidean distance when we measure distance between 1D points, but how about images? Hence, for general solution we will need something that works universally. And that is what [Wasserstein GAN paper](https://arxiv.org/abs/1701.07875) is about. \n",
        "\n",
        "For the sake of this post, we will skip the details of how and why WGAN works (there are a few brilliant posts about that, please checkout out links in \"Further reading\" section below), but to put it simply, we can use the distance between the outputs of the discriminator as proxy for distances between distributions. However, there is one important condition: we have to enforce a Lipschitz constraint. We will ignore Lipschitz constraint for now. "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ipYY7Ip5uXfm",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "Let's try it out. "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "58zy1jHr75vt",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "We measure the distance between the outputs of discriminator by simply distracting"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "34mW4sVr8De9",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "colab": {}
      },
      "source": [
        "def d_loss_wgan(d_score_z, d_score_r):\n",
        "  return tf.reduce_mean(d_score_z - d_score_r)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "iYx_MkQk2pEW",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "outputId": "2f12faea-6e33-4eb7-f4ff-10b9b2530b08",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 201
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "discriminator_wgan, d_optimizer = define_discriminator(act=None)\n",
        "train_discriminator(discriminator_wgan, d_optimizer, d_loss_wgan)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Total loss: -0.20631 Scores for real: 0.0 Scores for generated: -0.20631\n",
            "Total loss: -92241.375 Scores for real: -128.61824 Scores for generated: -92370.0\n",
            "Total loss: -1122561.8 Scores for real: -766.5613 Scores for generated: -1123328.2\n",
            "Total loss: -4381084.5 Scores for real: -1648.9462 Scores for generated: -4382733.5\n",
            "Total loss: -11101716.0 Scores for real: -2930.0134 Scores for generated: -11104646.0\n",
            "Total loss: -20111968.0 Scores for real: -2881.5947 Scores for generated: -20114848.0\n",
            "Total loss: -37373372.0 Scores for real: -2529.8655 Scores for generated: -37375904.0\n",
            "Total loss: -62526256.0 Scores for real: -10314.391 Scores for generated: -62536570.0\n",
            "Total loss: -69934790.0 Scores for real: -9289.29 Scores for generated: -69944080.0\n",
            "Total loss: -135784350.0 Scores for real: -2764.6501 Scores for generated: -135787120.0\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "uaTk0jQl8F_w",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "Looks like it is working, loss is decreasing, although it is quite unusual to see negative loss"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "qVJVtzLZ8V3j",
        "colab_type": "text"
      },
      "source": [
        "So now we have discriminator which gives high scores for real examples. So the objective for generator would be to get as high scores as possible, hence we need just `-discriminator(generated)`"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mntVyJ69RbXr",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "outputId": "40935c46-83a6-4764-bae1-d93ded552606",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 451
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "def g_loss_wgan(x):\n",
        "  return tf.reduce_mean(-discriminator_wgan(x))\n",
        "train_generator(g_loss_wgan)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 0,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Loss: 86786170.0 Generator output:  0.3962338\n",
            "Loss: 2060925.2 Generator output:  0.009125391\n",
